# JS/TS Review

When reviewing JavaScript/TypeScript code, check:

- **Correctness:** Logic and types are correct; no obvious bugs or misuse of APIs.
- **API stability:** Public API changes are intentional and documented; consider backward compatibility.
- **Types:** No unnecessary `any`; types are precise where they matter. TypeScript strictness respected if the project uses it.
- **Style and consistency:** Follow project style (ESLint, Prettier); consistent naming and structure.
- **Security:** Inputs validated; no sensitive data in logs or error messages.
- **Test adequacy:** New behavior has tests; existing tests still pass; edge cases considered.

Prioritize findings as **must-fix** (correctness, safety, API contract) vs **nice-to-have** (style, clarity).
